01:25.954 --> 01:28.289
Anastasia?

01:29.626 --> 01:31.093
Stop.

01:37.000 --> 01:39.435
Cuff yourself to the bedpost.

01:46.778 --> 01:49.346
Don't bother.

02:09.068 --> 02:14.107
You look good. Healthy.

02:14.175 --> 02:19.013
Pale, though. I think maybe
you live on the East Coast.

02:19.047 --> 02:24.351
For years I've been thinking...
"Where is she?

02:24.386 --> 02:28.522
Is she close or half the world away?

02:28.556 --> 02:32.660
Is she still nervous when it thunders?

02:32.694 --> 02:36.697
Does she remember
our walks in Coney Island?

02:36.731 --> 02:40.168
Getting borscht from Alexa's?"

02:48.678 --> 02:51.847
They're all there, every last one.

03:01.459 --> 03:04.127
And what do you want
in exchange for this?

03:05.196 --> 03:06.997
Just let me go.

03:08.867 --> 03:13.471
He found you faster than I thought.

03:13.505 --> 03:19.877
<i>He did in one week
what I failed to do in 15 years.</i>

03:19.912 --> 03:23.248
True love, huh?

03:23.282 --> 03:25.917
Just take the diamonds
and consider me dead.

03:25.952 --> 03:27.819
<i>Or what?</i>

03:27.854 --> 03:31.056
You've only given me
half of what I want.

03:33.292 --> 03:38.396
- I want him.
- I can't do that.

03:38.431 --> 03:41.533
If you could, you would be free.

03:49.176 --> 03:50.977
Your word?

03:52.113 --> 03:54.214
My word.

03:56.884 --> 04:01.788
Now...
how are you going to get away?

04:01.822 --> 04:04.157
There's something else
in the bag for you.

04:09.897 --> 04:13.867
<i>Clever Girl.</i>

04:35.323 --> 04:37.825
Bye, Daddy.

05:57.360 --> 06:00.387
<i><font color="cyan"> sync for DEMAND by achelec
~ addic7ed.com ~ </font></i>

06:11.618 --> 06:14.052
<i>- Say "champ." Say "champ."
- Champ!</i>

06:14.087 --> 06:16.187
<i>- Banshee, PA! What's up, baby?
- Mr. Sanchez,</i>

06:16.222 --> 06:18.056
what can you tell us
about this upcoming fight?

06:18.091 --> 06:20.425
What can I tell you about...
I can tell you'd better...

06:20.460 --> 06:22.661
Benjamin, this fight will
cement your credibility

06:22.696 --> 06:24.096
with the Gaming Commission.

06:24.131 --> 06:26.332
Give me another week,
and I'll have us cleared

06:26.366 --> 06:29.302
to break ground on the hotel.

06:29.336 --> 06:35.776
I must admit I had my doubts, Kai,
but you pulled it off.

06:35.843 --> 06:37.844
It's our casino.
We're putting up the purse.

06:37.878 --> 06:40.514
<i>- He was just the middleman.
- Alex, enough.</i>

06:40.548 --> 06:42.549
<i>The champ is in the
building, ladies and gentlemen.</i>

06:42.583 --> 06:44.417
<i>The champ is in the building.</i>

06:44.452 --> 06:46.553
Mr. Sanchez, Kai Proctor.

06:46.587 --> 06:48.454
- Welcome to Banshee.
- Glad to be here.

06:48.489 --> 06:51.224
This is Benjamin Longshadow.
His tribe runs the Kinaho Moon.

06:51.258 --> 06:53.526
- Chief.
- It's an honor to have you here.

06:53.594 --> 06:56.395
- Alex Longshadow.
- Oh, 'kay.

06:56.430 --> 06:58.531
Mr. Sanchez, if you
would do us the honor...

06:58.565 --> 07:00.767
a few shots with the
casino in the background.

07:00.801 --> 07:04.403
- Man, of... come on, man, of course.
- Right this way.

07:04.438 --> 07:07.340
Mr. Proctor,
Douglas Dern, Damien's manager.

07:07.375 --> 07:09.575
- We spoke on the phone.
- We did. Pleasure to meet you.

07:09.610 --> 07:12.779
You said the place was old.
You didn't say ancient.

07:12.813 --> 07:16.316
The Kinaho feel a powerful
connection to their past.

07:16.350 --> 07:20.020
<i>In the case of the Kinaho Moon,
a little too powerful, in my opinion.</i>

07:20.054 --> 07:21.888
I would have preferred to
have the new casino built

07:21.922 --> 07:27.160
before we hosted Mr. Sanchez,
but rest assured the money is real.

07:27.195 --> 07:30.264
Yeah, it had better be.

07:30.299 --> 07:33.001
<i>He's gonna look worse soon, I promise.</i>

07:34.603 --> 07:38.572
<i>Nice casino. Not bad.</i>

07:40.408 --> 07:42.843
<i>Not bad at all.</i>

07:49.751 --> 07:51.185
There it is, baby.

07:51.219 --> 07:54.388
<i>- That's where I do my thing.
- This way, Mr. Sanchez.</i>

07:58.226 --> 08:00.495
You don't approve.

08:03.332 --> 08:06.735
The hotel... the revenue it will
earn should be for our people.

08:06.769 --> 08:08.270
We shouldn't be including
a man like Proctor.

08:08.304 --> 08:13.108
A man like that
gets things done quickly.

08:13.142 --> 08:17.979
We're building something that will
sustain our tribe for years to come.

08:20.082 --> 08:25.186
When I go to the spirits,
I want to have seen the start of it all.

09:17.107 --> 09:19.809
Are you sure you wouldn't prefer
a hotel? It's just a quick call.

09:19.844 --> 09:21.770
I can have you in
the presidential suite.

09:21.771 --> 09:24.481
No, no, no.
My trailer goes wherever I go.

09:24.515 --> 09:26.650
I don't like to be too
pampered before a fight.

09:26.684 --> 09:28.718
Besides, there'll be
plenty of time for that

09:28.753 --> 09:30.620
after I put Hollister's noose up there.

09:30.655 --> 09:33.023
As agreed.

09:34.759 --> 09:36.660
Thank you.

09:39.430 --> 09:40.831
I think I like this town.

09:40.866 --> 09:43.301
We also made some
improvements on your bedroom.

09:43.335 --> 09:46.170
<i>I think you will be pleased.</i>

09:48.340 --> 09:53.512
<i> # Amazing Grace #</i>

09:53.547 --> 09:54.947
<i>♪ How sweet... ♪</i>

09:54.981 --> 10:00.087
<i>- Now I know I like this town.
- # The sound #</i>

10:00.121 --> 10:09.129
♪ That saved a wretch like me ♪

10:09.163 --> 10:15.168
♪ I once was lost ♪

10:15.202 --> 10:20.373
<i>♪ But now am found ♪</i>

10:20.408 --> 10:29.483
<i>♪ Was blind, but now I see ♪</i>

10:31.018 --> 10:35.889
<i>♪ 'Twas Grace that taught... ♪</i>

10:38.293 --> 10:40.995
Senator, you have the
Department's deepest sympathies.

10:41.029 --> 10:46.266
- Mrs. Schumacher, I'm so, so sorry.
- Sorry for your loss.

10:53.373 --> 10:55.107
Sorry, ma'am.

11:05.351 --> 11:07.253
<i>Sheriff Hood.</i>

11:07.320 --> 11:12.091
Gordon.
Hi, Deva.

11:12.125 --> 11:15.027
It's a pretty tough day for everyone.

11:15.062 --> 11:17.062
Yep.

11:20.767 --> 11:23.369
Say, why don't you join
us for dinner tonight?

11:23.403 --> 11:26.238
Nothing fancy; I'm just gonna grill
out some burgers in the back yard.

11:26.272 --> 11:31.744
- Oh, honey, you know...
- That sounds great. Thanks, Gordon.

11:32.746 --> 11:34.180
Why don't we say about 6:00?

11:34.214 --> 11:36.916
- Sure. See you there.
- Good.

11:44.257 --> 11:46.325
So, how do you like
your burger, Sheriff?

11:46.360 --> 11:48.494
Medium rare, thanks.

11:50.897 --> 11:52.931
- Can I see your gun?
- Yeah, sure.

11:52.966 --> 11:56.401
No. Thank you.
You don't need to see his gun.

11:56.435 --> 11:59.337
Hey, hon', why don't you
grab the Sheriff another beer?

11:59.371 --> 12:01.639
I'll get it, Mom.

12:01.674 --> 12:04.242
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

12:09.748 --> 12:10.915
Here you go.

12:10.949 --> 12:13.484
- Thank you.
- Yep.

12:16.388 --> 12:18.890
So, Deva, how are you doing?

12:20.793 --> 12:25.797
I don't know.
I still can't believe it.

12:25.832 --> 12:28.300
Yeah. It takes some time.

12:30.436 --> 12:34.640
- Deva, honey, would you go get...
- Yeah. Hold on, Maxie.

12:38.812 --> 12:41.113
Nice and deep, bubba.

12:42.949 --> 12:44.650
You okay?

12:44.684 --> 12:46.919
That's the way.

12:48.054 --> 12:49.888
<i> You good?</i>

12:54.995 --> 12:56.095
What's wrong with him?

12:56.129 --> 12:58.531
It's been happening
since he was a toddler.

13:00.133 --> 13:04.870
- Is he... is he okay?
- He has good days and bad days.

13:11.245 --> 13:13.996
Hey, Max,
why don't you go ahead

13:13.997 --> 13:17.783
and touch the gun
just for a second?

13:22.322 --> 13:23.458
Yeah.

13:29.162 --> 13:31.731
<i> You know, Sheriff,
we never got a chance</i>

13:31.732 --> 13:34.300
<i>to thank you for pulling Deva
out of that mess the other night.</i>

13:34.335 --> 13:38.338
Aw. So how
did the arraignments go?

13:38.372 --> 13:41.441
Well, all the men you arrested
identified this guy Hanson,

13:41.475 --> 13:42.943
<i>but apparently he's long gone.</i>

13:42.977 --> 13:45.745
<i>And either they don't
know or won't talk about</i>

13:45.780 --> 13:49.616
<i>where the skulls came from.
It's not that I can't guess.</i>

13:49.650 --> 13:52.553
Whores, gambling, drugs.

13:52.587 --> 13:54.721
All crooked roads in
Banshee lead to one man,

13:54.756 --> 13:56.857
and that's Kai Proctor.

14:01.262 --> 14:06.299
- I'll get us some more drinks, eh?
- Great.

14:13.808 --> 14:16.943
- Alone at last.
- Shut up.

14:20.147 --> 14:22.248
What happened?

14:25.552 --> 14:27.120
Heavy bag workout.

14:28.655 --> 14:33.660
Mm, not unless it was a bag of bones.

14:40.368 --> 14:43.238
Ana...

14:43.272 --> 14:48.844
- it's me.
- Mm, no, you're different.

14:48.879 --> 14:50.279
How?

14:52.583 --> 14:54.951
You used to be kind.

15:00.625 --> 15:03.360
You know...

15:03.394 --> 15:07.297
you get locked up,
forgotten about for 15 years,

15:07.331 --> 15:08.598
see how kind you feel after that.

15:08.633 --> 15:12.135
- Now, I know you're angry, but...
- Angry?

15:12.169 --> 15:14.404
You have no fuckin' idea.

15:23.614 --> 15:25.282
<i> Hey, where are you going?</i>

15:25.316 --> 15:28.285
Uh, I got a call.
Thanks for the food.

15:58.682 --> 16:02.185
Look, um,
you wanna talk about it?

16:13.831 --> 16:15.465
Drinking alone?

16:22.339 --> 16:25.908
<i>- To keeping secrets.
- # Downing my whiskey #</i>

16:25.943 --> 16:31.416
<i>♪ It's all the same ♪</i>

16:31.450 --> 16:35.952
<i>♪ Tobacco in the sunshine... ♪</i>

16:35.986 --> 16:39.656
- Hey, um...
- Rebecca.

16:39.690 --> 16:42.225
Rebecca.

16:43.794 --> 16:45.628
I think you should go home.

16:47.598 --> 16:51.702
<i>♪ Downing my whiskey ♪</i>

16:51.736 --> 16:54.404
<i>♪ It's all the same... ♪</i>

16:54.439 --> 16:56.073
No, you don't.

17:00.044 --> 17:03.680
What, are you...
saving yourself for someone?

17:11.457 --> 17:15.259
- Rebecca, we can't...
- Shut up.

17:18.195 --> 17:22.933
<i>♪ It's all the same,
it's all the same... ♪</i>

17:27.472 --> 17:31.108
Look, you told me to call
if she came back again.

17:31.176 --> 17:33.510
Well, she's back.

17:39.950 --> 17:42.485
<i>♪ Downing my whiskey... ♪</i>

18:08.178 --> 18:11.180
Hi, Uncle Kai.

18:11.214 --> 18:12.982
Don't you think you're
getting a little too old

18:13.016 --> 18:15.618
for this rebel streak of yours?

18:19.391 --> 18:21.859
That's rich coming from you.

18:25.831 --> 18:30.735
Whatever you may think,
my choices have cost me dearly.

18:30.769 --> 18:34.572
Yeah. You're really hurting.

18:35.875 --> 18:38.876
My mother lives just
10 miles away from me.

18:38.911 --> 18:42.046
I haven't seen or spoken
to her in over 20 years.

18:42.113 --> 18:46.150
My father, when I run into him,
won't even fucking look at me.

18:46.184 --> 18:49.954
My sister, your mother,
denies I even exist.

18:49.988 --> 18:53.157
Yeah, well, that's why
they call it being shunned.

18:53.192 --> 18:55.359
<i>Show some respect!</i>

18:58.831 --> 19:01.199
<i>I'm sorry, Uncle.</i>

19:02.701 --> 19:05.970
You can't begin to
understand how alone I am.

19:06.005 --> 19:08.439
I've lost count of the people I hurt,

19:08.474 --> 19:12.076
and still I hurt people every day.

19:14.113 --> 19:17.448
You have no idea what
that does to you inside.

19:20.052 --> 19:25.123
It's like a blade in your belly
that has gradually scraped you raw.

19:26.292 --> 19:28.827
I'm not buying it, Uncle.

19:28.861 --> 19:35.335
You have everything you've
ever wanted. You're free.

19:38.206 --> 19:41.475
Why don't you just admit
that you like being bad?

19:48.251 --> 19:54.056
Do you realize
no one else can talk to me like that?

19:54.091 --> 19:59.329
You're the only person who
isn't scared of me. The only one.

20:16.382 --> 20:18.349
I'll drive you home.

20:27.859 --> 20:30.027
<i> I want to welcome
our Camp Genoa Marines</i>

20:30.095 --> 20:32.797
<i>to view a private sparring
session with the champ.</i>

20:32.831 --> 20:35.299
<i>All right, ladies and gentlemen,</i>

20:35.334 --> 20:38.569
<i>let me introduce a man
who needs no introduction...</i>

20:38.604 --> 20:41.272
<i>two-time cruiserweight
champion of the world,</i>

20:41.306 --> 20:43.841
<i>honorary referee for
this weekend's fight,</i>

20:43.876 --> 20:46.810
<i>Banshee's own Sugar Bates!</i>

20:52.651 --> 20:55.686
<i>Now, a special gift for Mr. Sanchez</i>

20:55.720 --> 20:58.856
<i>from our sponsors at
Stark-Himmel Timepieces...</i>

20:58.891 --> 21:02.526
<i>a solid gold watch with a
one-of-a-kind diamond bezel</i>

21:02.561 --> 21:04.461
<i>designed especially for the champ.</i>

21:04.496 --> 21:07.564
<i>This is yours. Wear it well.</i>

21:07.598 --> 21:10.334
You got my invitation
for the cocktail party tomorrow

21:10.335 --> 21:12.327
- and the fight on Saturday?
- I did.

21:12.328 --> 21:14.503
<i>Thank you, gentlemen.</i>

21:14.538 --> 21:17.973
<i>Hey, listen, man, I wanna give
a semper fi to all my jarheads</i>

21:18.008 --> 21:20.910
<i>from Banshee's Camp Genoa, all right?</i>

21:20.944 --> 21:23.812
Seems like you're always
hosting something around here.

21:25.582 --> 21:27.483
<i>Y'all ready to see me whip some ass?</i>

21:27.517 --> 21:29.418
<i>- Yeah!
- Yeah!</i>

21:29.453 --> 21:31.554
You just came in to see him train?

21:31.588 --> 21:34.223
No. Actually, I came to see you.

21:35.726 --> 21:38.894
You heard about the
Schumacher boy OD'ing, right?

21:40.030 --> 21:43.833
Yeah, I did. It's terrible.

21:46.337 --> 21:51.074
Proctor, you told me you had a talent
for resolving problems here in Banshee.

21:53.311 --> 21:56.012
I was kind of hoping you
could help me with this one.

21:57.448 --> 22:00.285
I found these
in the dead boy's pocket.

22:01.387 --> 22:06.157
The kids call them "skulls."
You ever seen pills like that before?

22:06.191 --> 22:08.626
Are you asking me or accusing me?

22:08.660 --> 22:11.262
Why, I'm asking you, Kai.

22:12.464 --> 22:14.098
Just don't play games with me, Sheriff.

22:14.132 --> 22:15.966
I'm well aware of
Mayor Kendall's agenda.

22:16.001 --> 22:17.734
Oh, this has nothing to do with Kendall.

22:17.769 --> 22:20.270
The boy means well, but he's an idiot.

22:20.305 --> 22:25.041
On that at least I'm sure we can agree.
So if you'll excuse me...

22:26.844 --> 22:29.278
I'm busy trying to bring
good things to Banshee.

22:31.014 --> 22:32.847
Thanks for your time.

22:47.496 --> 22:50.197
- Asshole.
- What?

22:50.232 --> 22:52.700
You gotta watch me.
If you blink, it's over.

22:52.734 --> 22:56.003
He didn't have to hit him that
hard. They're just sparring.

22:59.274 --> 23:01.409
<i> Damn, I'm out of partners.</i>

23:01.443 --> 23:03.544
<i> Right here!
Sarge will take you on!</i>

23:05.948 --> 23:07.748
<i>Hey, hey, hey.</i>

23:07.783 --> 23:11.819
Ahem. 5-0.
Yeah, Sheriff.

23:13.021 --> 23:14.755
You want a shot at the title?

23:18.293 --> 23:19.894
Huh?
You can't throw a few punches?

23:27.036 --> 23:30.104
Go easy on him.
I'd be scared of me, too.

23:30.138 --> 23:32.239
<i> You're the champ!</i>

23:32.274 --> 23:33.507
<i> The Sheriff too smart.</i>

23:33.542 --> 23:36.844
He don't wanna step in the ring.
He don't want none of this.

23:42.183 --> 23:44.218
Excuse me, excuse me.

23:44.252 --> 23:45.886
<i>Hey. Can you come here?</i>

23:45.920 --> 23:47.488
Hey, hey. Hey, doll.

23:47.522 --> 23:50.023
- How you doing? What's your name?
- Chloe.

23:50.058 --> 23:52.526
Hey, um, Chloe, can you bring
me a bottle of champagne?

23:52.560 --> 23:56.229
- Sure. I'll be right back.
- No, doll.

23:56.264 --> 23:59.432
Can you bring it to my trailer?
Say, tonight around 11:00?

24:05.105 --> 24:08.207
- All right, Mr. Sanchez.
- All right, Chloe.

24:08.242 --> 24:09.776
<i>All right.</i>

24:14.982 --> 24:18.418
Come on in.

24:20.688 --> 24:24.092
Hmm.
Must be 11:00.

25:06.167 --> 25:08.502
<i>They're all there.</i>

25:13.108 --> 25:17.846
Just take them and go.
You can start a new life somewhere.

25:19.316 --> 25:22.518
You deserve that after
everything you've been through.

25:37.902 --> 25:43.073
You think you can buy me off? Huh?

25:43.108 --> 25:48.780
You listen to me.
I'm not going anywhere.

25:48.814 --> 25:52.450
So take your fuckin'
diamonds and get out.

26:21.813 --> 26:26.751
- You want a bump?
- I never have.

26:31.157 --> 26:32.791
I'll try.

26:34.261 --> 26:36.229
Yeah, fuck me harder.

26:37.698 --> 26:39.166
No, no, no, no.

26:39.200 --> 26:42.836
No, doll, no. Not like that.

26:42.871 --> 26:45.005
Like this.

26:50.546 --> 26:52.481
You like it like that?

26:59.588 --> 27:02.057
Fuck me harder!

27:19.708 --> 27:21.609
Ah, you're hurting me.

27:25.247 --> 27:28.249
No! Get off me!

27:28.283 --> 27:32.353
- Don't!
- Shut the fuck up!

27:39.862 --> 27:42.764
- Fucking bitch!
- Ah!

27:51.040 --> 27:52.541
Oh, my head!

28:01.285 --> 28:05.621
We have combed the entire building,
reviewed all security footage.

28:05.655 --> 28:11.593
- She left absolutely nothing behind.
- But she came.

28:11.627 --> 28:15.796
She walked right into the lion's den.

28:16.965 --> 28:20.000
He has become a threat to her.

28:21.236 --> 28:27.674
He has been locked up for 15 years.
He's sick with love.

28:27.709 --> 28:33.014
He is reckless.
And rusty.

28:34.082 --> 28:36.183
He'll make a mistake.

28:37.085 --> 28:42.090
He already did.
He scared her.

28:48.798 --> 28:51.032
I thought this was your day off.

28:52.468 --> 28:55.236
I don't have much of a social life.

28:58.841 --> 29:04.613
Do you miss being home?
You don't really talk about it.

29:08.852 --> 29:11.487
It must be hard coming to
a new town not knowing anyone.

29:12.824 --> 29:15.892
I'm used to being alone.

29:20.398 --> 29:23.166
I'll never get used to it.

29:42.717 --> 29:44.551
- Sheriff.
- Yeah.

29:44.585 --> 29:46.219
You need to get over to the hospital.

29:48.856 --> 29:53.827
<i>Chloe, I'm so sorry
I have to ask these questions.</i>

29:55.861 --> 29:58.365
<i>I'm almost done, okay?</i>

29:58.399 --> 29:59.900
So you and Mr. Sanchez...

29:59.967 --> 30:03.304
<i>being in bed together was consensual?</i>

30:04.673 --> 30:07.041
Until it got rough.

30:08.878 --> 30:10.813
I did something wrong
and he just...

30:10.847 --> 30:14.082
Chloe, look at me.

30:14.117 --> 30:17.319
You did nothing wrong, okay?

30:19.756 --> 30:22.925
He kicked me
and then he punched me.

30:22.959 --> 30:25.394
I was crawling.
I was trying to get away,

30:25.429 --> 30:28.030
<i>but he...
he wouldn't let...</i>

30:28.064 --> 30:32.668
then he...
took the champagne bottle...

30:35.772 --> 30:37.473
<i> Okay.</i>

30:38.642 --> 30:41.210
